headline: 1 Restaurant Stock on Our Buy List and 2 to Avoid
summary: Restaurants increase convenience and give many people a place to unwind. But it’s not all sunshine and rainbows as they’re notoriously hard to run thanks to perishable ingredients, labor shortages, or volatile consumer spending. Unfortunately, these factors have spelled trouble for the industry as it has shed 3.9% over the past six months. This performance was disappointing since the S&P 500 held steady.

headline: March 2025 Stocks That May Be Priced Below Estimated Value
summary: As the U.S. stock market faces turbulence due to impending auto tariffs and a tech sector selloff, investors are increasingly vigilant about identifying opportunities amid uncertainty. In this climate, undervalued stocks—those priced below their estimated intrinsic value—can offer potential for growth as they may be overlooked by the broader market sentiment.
